The GROUP BY clause in SQL is used to arrange identical data into groups.
Itâ€™s mostly used with aggregate functions like:

COUNT() â€“ count rows

SUM() â€“ total

AVG() â€“ average

MIN() â€“ smallest value

MAX() â€“ largest value

ðŸ”¹ Basic Syntax
SELECT column_name, AGGREGATE_FUNCTION(column_name)
FROM table_name
